## Decisions Made
- validate failed path delegates loop-state cleanup to candidate clear instead of writing both stores: prevents cross-skill state coupling and keeps validate focused on WI-level concerns
- candidate clear demoted path made idempotent (skip WI write if already demoted by validate): chosen over alternative of having validate not write WI changes at all, because validate is the natural owner of WI status transitions
- Mode Transition Protocol uses an explicit 12-row table with invalid-transition rejection: formal protocol over implicit convention to prevent state machine drift
- Review findings persisted to disk (.agent-atelier/reviews/<WI-ID>/findings.json): enables cold resume without re-running review synthesis
- execute requeue accepts any non-terminal status including reviewing with promotion metadata cleanup: enables AUTOFIX cycle from review phase
- on-prompt.sh collects 3 signals (open gates, active_candidate, pending WAL) via python3 inline: chosen over shell-only approach for JSON parsing reliability

## Problems Encountered
- validate/candidate double-write discovered during production readiness review: validate and candidate clear both wrote the same WI demotion changes. Resolved by making candidate clear idempotent.
- REVIEW_SYNTHESIS phase text in run SKILL.md was missing the clean-review-to-IMPLEMENT transition that existed in the transition table. Resolved by adding the missing transition to phase text.
- on-prompt.sh missing trailing newline after JSON output. Resolved by adding print() after json.dump.
- AGENTS.md listed 8 role prompts but 10 existed on disk (ui-designer, aesthetic-ux-reviewer were missing from the count). Resolved by updating count and list.

## Constraints Identified
- Single active_candidate slot is exclusive — only one candidate under validation at a time. This serialization is an invariant from the state schema.
- Information barrier between implementation and validation must be enforced at every phase boundary — VRM never sees Builder context.
- All state writes must go through state-commit (sole writer guarantee) — no direct file writes to .agent-atelier/.

